n Awards - Disney+ Hotstar|website=Disney+\u00a0Hotstar|language=en|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Bala (2019 film)|Bala]]\n|[[Zee Cine Awards]]\n|[[Zee Cine Award for Best Actor in a Supporting Role \u2013 Female|Best Supporting Actress]]\n|{{won}}\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.desimartini.com/news/martini-shots/trending/zee-cine-awards-2020-here-are-the-winners-article136366.htm|title=ZEE CINE AWARDS 2020: Here is The Complete Winners List|date=2020-03-14|website=Desimartini|language=en|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref>\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category}}\n* {{IMDb name|6277267}}\n* [https://www.bollywoodhungama.com/celebrity/bhumi-pednekar/ Bhumi Pednekar] on [[Bollywood Hungama]]\n\n{{Navboxes\n|title = Awards for Bhumi Pednekar\n|list=\n{{FilmfareAwardBestFemaleDebut}}\n{{FilmfareCriticsAwardBestActress}}\n{{ScreenAwardBestFemaleDebut}}\n{{IIFAAwardBestFemaleDebut}}\n{{Zee Cine Award for Best Female Debut}}\n}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Pednekar, Bhumi}}\n[[Category:1989 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Mumbai]]\n[[Category:Actresses in Hindi cinema]]\n[[Category:21st-century Indian actresses]]\n[[Category:Marathi people]]\n[[Category:Indian film actresses]]\n[[Category:Zee Cine Awards winners]]\n[[Category:Indian people of Marathi descent]]\n[[Category:People of Haryanvi descent]]\n", "name_user": "Jellysandwich0", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bhumi_Pednekar"}
{"title_page": "Palatine Wine Queen", "text_new": "[[File:Winzerfestzug 2009.jpg|thumb|Gabi Klein, Palatine Wine Queen in 2009/10, with two of her princesses at the Neustadt Wine Festival Parade]]\nThe '''Palatine Wine Queen''' ({{lang-de|Pf\u00e4lzische Weink\u00f6nigin}}), sometimes also called the '''Palatinate Wine Queen''',<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=-3KE92Z10r8C&q=%22palatinate+wine+queen%22&dq=%22palatinate+wine+queen%22&hl=en&sa=X&ei=eOJHUsTENsnA7Aa6wIGABA&ved=0CDYQ6AEwAQ ''An International Guide to the Wines of the World'' by John Morrell (1975)]</ref><ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=h1gbAQAAMAAJ&q=%22palatinate+wine+queen%22&dq=%22palatinate+wine+queen%22&hl=en&sa=X&ei=eOJHUsTENsnA7Aa6wIGABA&ved=0CDoQ6AEwAg ''The Bulletin, Vols 19-21''] by the Germany (West) Press and Information Office, 1971.</ref> is the annually elected representative of the [[Palatine wine region]], one of currently 13 recognized [[wine regions in Germany]]. She is eligible to participate, the following year, in the competition for the [[German Wine Queen]].\n\n== History ==\nIn 1931 the Palatinate region of Germany nominated a wine queen in the town of [[Neustadt an der Weinstra\u00dfe]] at the initiative of the publisher, Daniel Meininger, becoming the first of the German wine-growing regions to do so. The first wine queen was Ruth Bachrodt<ref name=\"hagen\">{{cite web |author=Lilo Hagen |title=Die Theysohns |url=http://www.lilo-hagen.de/die-theysohns.htm |access-date=2012-09-13 \n}} \u2013 Reference for the correct spelling of the name Bachrodt \u2013 mit dt</ref> of [[Pirmasens]] in the Southwest Palatinate. This part of the Palatinate has no vineyards and Bachrodt owed her election to the fact that the organizers felt she was the prettiest girl in the audience in the festival hall (the ''Saalbau'' in Neustadt) and the judges upheld their proposal.<ref name=\"bachrodt\">{{cite web |author=pfaelzische-weinkoenigin.de |title=Historisches |url=http://www.pfaelzische-weinkoenigin.de/kroenung/historisches.php |access-date=2012-09-13}}</ref> The  candidate had previously been asked the question, \"What does a wine queen in all circumstances?\" Bachrodt had replied, \"you definitely need a pair of good shoes, so you can work in the vineyard.\" With that she also impressed the Pirmasens shoe manufacturer, Daniel Theysohn, and they were married in 1938.<ref name=\"hagen\" />\n\nBecause the Palatine Wine Queen in Germany was the only wine queen for many years, she also represented German wine as a whole until 1939 and then again from 1947 to 1949 without needing to go through any further competition. In 1949, too, there was only one competition, but subsequently [[Elizabeth Gies|Elisabeth Kuhn, later Gies]] from [[Diedesfeld]] officially became the [[German Wine Queen]] and was thus the only person to hold the titles of Palatine Wine Queen and German Wine Queen in the same year.<ref name=\"yoopress\">{{cite web |author=Arthur Wirtzfeld |title=Im k\u00f6niglichen R\u00fcckblick: Elisabeth Gies \u2013 German Wine Queen vor 60 Jahren |url=http://www.yoopress.com/de/weinnews/weinkollektive/dwi-deutsches-weininstitut/2932.Im_koeniglichen_Rueckblick_Elisabeth_Gies_-_German_Weinkoenigin_vor__Jahren.html |date=2010-09-01 |access-date=2012-09-13}}</ref>\n\n== Competition process ==\nThe election of the Palatine Wine Queen traditionally takes place during the [[German Wine Festival]], in the ''Saalbau'' in the town of [[Neustadt an der Weinstra\u00dfe]], on the Friday of the first weekend of the festival at the end of September or early October. After her year in office the Palatine Wine Queen, together with the  wine queens of the other twelve German wine regions, takes part in the competition to choose the German Wine Queen. In two years, the outgoing Palatine Wine Queen has been chosen as the German Wine Queen: \n[[Sylvia Benzinger]] in 2005 and [[Katja Schweder]] in 2006.\n\n== List of Palatine wine queens ==\n[[File:Pf Weinkoenigin0607.jpg|thumb|Julia Becker, Palatine Wine Queen in 2007/08]]\nThe following list shows all Palatine Wine Queens since the competition began in 1931:<ref>[http://www.pfaelzische-weinkoenigin.de/kroenung/koeniginnen.php ''Alle pf\u00e4lzischen Weink\u00f6niginnen seit 1931''] at www.pfaelzische-weinkoenigin.de. Accessed on 29 Sep 2013.</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" \n| width=\"100%\" |\n# 1931/32: Ruth Bachrodt, later Theysohn (born 9 Mar 1913; died 5 Mar 1997),<ref name=\"hagen\" /><ref name=\"theyson\">{{cite web |author=[[S\u00fcdwestrundfunk]] |title=Unternehmer: Daniel Theysohn \u2013 Archiv |url=http://www.swr.de/archiv/regionen/100-groessten-rheinland-pfaelzer/kandidaten/-/id=2616472/nid=2616472/did=2873206/1lvtmlm/index.html |access-date=2012-09-13}}</ref><ref name=\"schehl\">{{cite web |author=Dieter Schehl |title=Wasgauer Gespr\u00e4che |url=http://www.umdenken.de/cweb/cgi-bin-noauth/cache/VAL_BLOB/1154/1154/634/vortrag%2520schehl%25202002.DOC&sa=U&ei=7YhRULb7LMfbsgbHvoGgBQ&ved=0CCYQFjAH&usg=AFQjCNH8h43InwsslO2w8r3n5XM_8H_-Kg |access-date=2012-09-13 }} \u2013 Word document with Bachrodt\u2019s DOB, reference for correct spelling of the name of Bachrodt \u2013 mit dt</ref> [[Pirmasens]]\n# 1932/33: Cilly Seitz, [[Rhodt unter Rietburg|Rhodt]]\n# 1933/34: Gertrud D\u00f6rr, [[Wachenheim an der Weinstra\u00dfe|Wachenheim]]\n# 1934/35: Trudel Knauber, [[Billigheim]]\n# 1935/36: Hilde K\u00f6hler, [[Gimmeldingen]]\n# 1936/37: Elisabeth Fitz, later Keller, [[Edenkoben]]\n# 1937/38: Gustel Hauptmann, [[Haardt (Neustadt)|Haardt]]\n# 1938/39: Maria Poh, [[Hambach an der Weinstra\u00dfe|Hambach]]\n# 1947/48: Ilse Kurz, [[Mu\u00dfbach (Neustadt)|Mu\u00dfbach]]\n# 1948/49: C\u00e4cilia Hormuth, [[Sankt Martin (Palatinate)|St. Martin]]\n# 1949/50: [[Elisabeth Gies|Elisabeth Kuhn, later Gies]], [[Diedesfeld]]\n# 1950/51: Trudel Keller, [[Bad D\u00fcrkheim]]\n# 1951/52: Marlies Lack, Bad D\u00fcrkheim\n# 1952/53: Anneliese Bender, [[Gleisweiler]]\n# 1953/54: Ingrid Schreck, later Seyler, [[Deidesheim]]\n# 1954/55: Rosemarie Reibold, [[Freinsheim]]\n# 1955/56: Annemarie M\u00fcller, Haardt\n# 1956/57: Ilse Reinig, later Rodach, [[Edesheim]]\n# 1957/58: Doris Christmann, St. Martin\n# 1958/59: Renate Poh, Hambach\n# 1959/60: Christel Koch, [[Ungstein]]\n# 1960/61: B\u00e4rbel Christa H\u00e4rle, Mu\u00dfbach\n# 1961/62: Sieglinde Jung, [[Siebeldingen]]\n# 1962/63: Inge Bender, [[Kallstadt]]\n# 1963/64: Waltraud Lohr, [[Obrigheim (Palatinate)|Obrigheim]]\n# 1964/65: Waltraud Hey, [[Oberotterbach]]\n# 1965/66: Heidi Eberle, [[Laumersheim]]\n# 1966/67: Ulrike Klein, [[Rhodt unter Rietburg|Rhodt]]\n# 1967/68: Christa Jung, Siebeldingen\n# 1968/69: Heidrun Reim, Mu\u00dfbach\n# 1969/70: Gretel Stachel, [[Maikammer]]\n# 1970/71: Ruth Kr\u00f6ther, Freinsheim\n# 1971/72: Melitta Engel (born 24 Mar 1952; died 8 Sep 2012), Obrigheim\n# 1972/73: Helga Weber, [[Weisenheim am Sand]]\n# 1973/74: Siegrid Betz, Wachenheim\n# 1974/75: Annette Oehl, later G\u00f6b, [[Forst an der Weinstra\u00dfe|Forst]]\n# 1975/76: Maritta M\u00fcller, Hambach\n# 1976/77: Ingrid Grimm, [[Schweigen-Rechtenbach|Schweigen]]\n# 1977/78: Heidrun Winkelmann, Gimmeldingen\n# 1978/79: Christa Brauch, [[Birkweiler]]\n# 1979/80: Heike Bohnenstiel, later Voss, [[Herxheim am Berg]]\n# 1980/81: Hildegard Weber, [[G\u00f6nnheim]]\n# 1981/82: Gaby Br\u00fcckmann, Freinsheim\n# 1982/83: Claudia H\u00e4nling, [[Heuchelheim-Klingen|Heuchelheim]]\n# 1983/84: Sigrun Stutzmann, [[Einselthum]]\n# 1984/85: Heidrun Wolf, Birkweiler\n# 1985/86: Maria Bergold, Wachenheim\n# 1986/87: Ulrike Peter, Bad D\u00fcrkheim\n# 1987/88: Annette Borell, later Borell-Diehl, [[Hainfeld (Palatinate)|Hainfeld]]\n# 1988/89: Anne Brauner, later Fischer, [[G\u00f6cklingen]]\n# 1989/90: Birgit Schehl, later Rebholz-Schehl (born 1969), Hainfeld\n# 1990/91: Diane Blaul, later Fehling (born 25. Juli 1973), G\u00f6nnheim\n# 1991/92: Birgit Weisbrod, later Lorenz, Freinsheim\n# 1992/93: [[Christine Schneider]] (born 5 Jun 1972), [[Edenkoben]]\n# 1993/94: Claudia Heupel, later Hoffmann, [[Nu\u00dfdorf (Landau)|Nu\u00dfdorf]]\n# 1994/95: Silke Gerner, later Wolz (born 1972), Weisenheim am Sand\n# 1995/96: Monika Metz, [[Pleisweiler-Oberhofen|Pleisweiler]]\n# 1996/97: Sonja Freund, later Freund-Kuhmann, Bad D\u00fcrkheim\n# 1997/98: Jasmin M\u00fcller, [[Landau in der Pfalz|Landau]]\n# 1998/99: Eva Wendel (born 1 Aug 1975), [[Bissersheim]]\n# 1999/2000: Birgit Winkler, [[Steinweiler]]\n# 2000/01: Anke Schmitt, Bad D\u00fcrkheim\n# 2001/02: Tanja Schmidt, Deidesheim\n# 2002/03: Barbara Klein (born 28 Dec 1981), Hainfeld\n# 2003/04: Tina Kiefer (born 26 Feb 1981), [[Ranschbach]]\n# 2004/05: [[Sylvia Benzinger|Sylvia Benzinger, later Benzinger-Kugler]] (born 16 Aug 1978), [[Kirchheim an der Weinstra\u00dfe|Kirchheim]]\n# 2005/06: [[Katja Schweder]] (born 15 Jun 1980), [[Hochstadt (Palatinate)|Hochstadt]]\n# 2006/07: Susanne Winterling (born 1 Dec 1986), [[Niederkirchen bei Deidesheim|Niederkirchen]]\n# 2007/08: Julia Becker (born 28 Sep 1982), [[Edesheim]]\n# 2008/09: Patricia Frank (born 1 Oct 1985), [[Bockenheim an der Weinstra\u00dfe|Bockenheim]]\n# 2009/10: Gabi Klein (born 8 Mar 1987), Diedesfeld\n# 2010/11: Karen Storck (born 23 Feb 1988), Einselthum\n# 2011/12: Anna Katharina Hochd\u00f6rffer (born 27 Sep 1988), Nu\u00dfdorf\n# 2012/13: Andrea R\u00f6mmich (born 30 Nov 1988), Edenkoben\n# 2013/14: [[Janina Huhn]] (* 25 October 1989), Bad D\u00fcrkheim\n# 2014/15: Laura Julier (* 16 April 1991), Hambach\n# 2015/16: Julia Kren, [[Meckenheim (Pfalz)|Meckenheim]]\n# 2016/17: Anastasia Kronauer (* 2 May 1992), [[Lachen-Speyerdorf]]\n# 2017/18: Inga Storck (* 21 July 1994), Einselthum<ref>Schwester der 72. Weink\u00f6nigin Karen Storck (2010/11).</ref>\n# 2018/19: Meike Klohr (* 1994), Mu\u00dfbach<ref>{{cite web|title=Meike Klohr zur 80. Pf\u00e4lzischen Weink\u00f6nigin gew\u00e4hlt|periodical=[[Die Rheinpfalz]]|publisher=|url=https://www.rheinpfalz.de/lokal/artikel/meike-klohr-zur-80-pfaelzischen-weinkoenigin-gewaehlt-mit-bilderstrecke-und-video/|url-status=|format=|access-date=2018-10-06|archive-url=|archive-date=|last=mk/pah (Autorenk\u00fcrzel)|date=2018-10-05|year=|language=|pages=|quote=}}</ref>\n# 2019/20: Anna-Maria L\u00f6ffler, [[Ha\u00dfloch]]\n|}\n\n== German Wine Queens from the Palatinate ==\n[[File:Katja_Schweder.JPG|thumb|Katja Schweder als German Wine Queen]]\nTo date the following representatives from the [[Palatinate (wine region)|Palatine wine region]] have been crowned as [[German Wine Queen]]:\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" \n| width=\"100%\" |\n# 1949/50: [[Elisabeth Gies|Elisabeth Kuhn, later Gies]]\n# 1955/56: Irmgard Mohler (did not previously hold the title of Palatine Wine Queen)\n# 1960/61: Christel Koch\n# 1965/66: Waltraud Hey\n# 1971/72: Ruth Kr\u00f6ther\n# 1981/82: Hildegard Weber\n# 1990/91: Birgit Schehl\n# 2005/06: [[Sylvia Benzinger]]\n# 2006/07: [[Katja Schweder]]\n|}\n\n== References ==\n<references />\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://www.pfaelzische-weinkoenigin.de/ Website of the current Palatine Wine Queen]\n* [http://www.pfaelzische-weinkoenigin.de/kroenung/koeniginnen.php List of all Palatine Wine Queens] since 1931\n\n{{German Wine Queens}}\n\n[[Category:German Wine Queens|!]]\n", "text_old": "[[File:Winzerfestzug 2009.jpg|thumb|Gabi Klein, Palatine Wine Queen in 2009/10, with two of her princesses at the Neustadt Wine Festival Parade]]\nThe '''Palatine Wine Queen''' ({{lang-de|Pf\u00e4lzische Weink\u00f6nigin}}), sometimes also called the '''Palatinate Wine Queen''',<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=-3KE92Z10r8C&q=%22palatinate+wine+queen%22&dq=%22palatinate+wine+queen%22&hl=en&sa=X&ei=eOJHUsTENsnA7Aa6wIGABA&ved=0CDYQ6AEwAQ ''An International Guide to the Wines of the World'' by John Morrell (1975)]</ref><ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=h1gbAQAAMAAJ&q=%22palatinate+wine+queen%22&dq=%22palatinate+wine+queen%22&hl=en&sa=X&ei=eOJHUsTENsnA7Aa6wIGABA&ved=0CDoQ6AEwAg ''The Bulletin, Vols 19-21''] by the Germany (West) Press and Information Office, 1971.</ref> is the annually elected representative of the [[Palatine wine region]], one of currently 13 recognized [[wine regions in Germany]]. She is eligible to participate, the following year, in the competition for the [[German Wine Queen]].\n\n== History ==\nIn 1931 the Palatinate region of Germany nominated a wine queen in the town of [[Neustadt an der Weinstra\u00dfe]] at the initiative of the publisher, Daniel Meininger, becoming the first of the German wine-growing regions to do so. The first wine queen was Ruth Bachrodt<ref name=\"hagen\">{{cite web |author=Lilo Hagen |title=Die Theysohns |url=http://www.lilo-hagen.de/die-theysohns.htm |access-date=2012-09-13 \n}} \u2013 Reference for the correct spelling of the name Bachrodt \u2013 mit dt</ref> of [[Pirmasens]] in the Southwest Palatinate. This part of the Palatinate has no vineyards and Bachrodt owed her election to the fact that the organizers felt she was the prettiest girl in the audience in the festival hall (the ''Saalbau'' in Neustadt) and the judges upheld their proposal.<ref name=\"bachrodt\">{{cite web |author=pfaelzische-weinkoenigin.de |title=Historisches |url=http://www.pfaelzische-weinkoenigin.de/kroenung/historisches.php |access-date=2012-09-13}}</ref> The  candidate had previously been asked the question, \"What does a wine queen in all circumstances?\" Bachrodt had replied, \"you definitely need a pair of good shoes, so you can work in the vineyard.\" With that she also impressed the Pirmasens shoe manufacturer, Daniel Theysohn, and they were married in 1938.<ref name=\"hagen\" />\n\nBecause the Palatine Wine Queen in Germany was the only wine queen for many years, she also represented German wine as a whole until 1939 and then again from 1947 to 1949 without needing to go through any further competition. In 1949, too, there was only one competition, but subsequently [[Elizabeth Gies|Elisabeth Kuhn, later Gies]] from [[Diedesfeld]] officially became the [[German Wine Queen]] and was thus the only person to hold the titles of Palatine Wine Queen and German Wine Queen in the same year.<ref name=\"yoopress\">{{cite web |author=Arthur Wirtzfeld |title=Im k\u00f6niglichen R\u00fcckblick: Elisabeth Gies \u2013 German Wine Queen vor 60 Jahren |url=http://www.yoopress.com/de/weinnews/weinkollektive/dwi-deutsches-weininstitut/2932.Im_koeniglichen_Rueckblick_Elisabeth_Gies_-_German_Weinkoenigin_vor__Jahren.html |date=2010-09-01 |access-date=2012-09-13}}</ref>\n\n== Competition process ==\nThe election of the Palatine Wine Queen traditionally takes place during the [[German Wine Festival]], in the ''Saalbau'' in the town of [[Neustadt an der Weinstra\u00dfe]], on the Friday of the first weekend of the festival at the end of September or early Oktober. After her year in office the Palatine Wine Queen, together with the  wine queens of the other twelve German wine regions, takes part in the competition to choose the German Wine Queen. In two years, the outgoing Palatine Wine Queen has been chosen as the German Wine Queen: \n[[Sylvia Benzinger]] in 2005 and [[Katja Schweder]] in 2006.\n\n== List of Palatine wine queens ==\n[[File:Pf Weinkoenigin0607.jpg|thumb|Julia Becker, Palatine Wine Queen in 2007/08]]\nThe following list shows all Palatine Wine Queens since the competition began in 1931:<ref>[http://www.pfaelzische-weinkoenigin.de/kroenung/koeniginnen.php ''Alle pf\u00e4lzischen Weink\u00f6niginnen seit 1931''] at www.pfaelzische-weinkoenigin.de. Accessed on 29 Sep 2013.</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" \n| width=\"100%\" |\n# 1931/32: Ruth Bachrodt, later Theysohn (born 9 Mar 1913; died 5 Mar 1997),<ref name=\"hagen\" /><ref name=\"theyson\">{{cite web |author=[[S\u00fcdwestrundfunk]] |title=Unternehmer: Daniel Theysohn \u2013 Archiv |url=http://www.swr.de/archiv/regionen/100-groessten-rheinland-pfaelzer/kandidaten/-/id=2616472/nid=2616472/did=2873206/1lvtmlm/index.html |access-date=2012-09-13}}</ref><ref name=\